";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=3406\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:552:\"<p>WordPress has over 50,000 plugins and finding quality free and premium plugins can be a daunting task to say the least! I&#8217;ve been in the WordPress community for over 10 years and I know this first hand. The goal of this guide is to help you save time and money by providing you with a definitive&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-plugins/\">Best WordPress Plugins &#8211; The Definitive Guide (2018)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Turner\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47890:\"<p>WordPress has over 50,000 plugins and finding quality free and premium plugins can be a <em>daunting task </em>to say the least! I&#8217;ve been in the WordPress community for over 10 years and I know this first hand.</p>\n<p>The goal of this guide is to help you save time and money by providing you with a definitive resource to the best free and paid plugin plugins and in various categories. No more spending hours downloading countless plugins just to test and see if they work and no more wasting money buying plugins from hack premium plugin authors.</p>\n<p><strong>Why should you listen to me?</strong></p>\n<p>I am a professional plugin developer turned business owner with over 15 years development experience and my free WordPress plugins have been downloaded over 5 million times. My <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/coming-soon/\" rel=\"noopener\">free coming soon page plugin</a> for WordPress is a top 100 plugin on WordPress.org. I have loved serving the WordPress community for the past 5+ years and want to give this guide back.</p>\n<p>Many of the plugins I&#8217;ll be recommending, I know the plugin authors behind the plugin and can vouch for all them when I say they are made by people who love the WordPress community. Many of them contribute to WordPress core, help run local meetups and WordCamps, attend WordCamp and are active members in the community.</p>\n<p>So without further ado here the <strong>Best Plugins for WordPress Guide for 2018</strong>.<br />\n<small>(Note: There are absolutely no affiliate links in this guide, it&#8217;s just my honest opinion from my many years of experience.)</small></p>\n<h2 id=\"plugin-categories\">Plugin Categories</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#backup-plugins\">Best BackUp Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#caching-plugins\">Best Caching Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#forms-plugins\">Best Forms (Contact Form) Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#calendar-plugin\">Best Calendar Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#social-sharing-plugin\">Best Social Sharing Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#best-site-migration-plugin\">Best Site Migration Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#security-plugins\">Best Security Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#lead-capture\">Best Lead Capture and Pop Up Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#page-builders\">Best Page Builder Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#image-gallery\">Best Image Gallery Plugin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#coming-soon\">Best Coming Soon and Maintenance Mode Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#google-analytics\">Best Google Analytics Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecommerce\">Best eCommerce Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#membership\">Best Membership Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#podcasting\">Best Podcasting Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#seo\">Best SEO Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#shortlink\">Best Shortlink / Affiliate Cloaking Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#custom-content-type\">Best Custom Content Type and Fields Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#misc\">Best Miscellaneous Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"backup-plugins\">Best BackUp Plugins</h2>\n<p>A Backup plugin is the number one plugin you should install on your WordPress site even before you install a <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">Coming Soon plugin</a>.  Lose any amount of work or a site just once and you&#8217;ll understand why. Fortunately it&#8217;s easy to do backups with these two plugins. I recommend these plugins depending on if the site is for yourself or for a client.</p>\n<p>If you are building WordPress sites for clients I recommend <a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/?utm_source=seedprod.com\">BackupBuddy by iThemes</a>.  They have a license that lets you cost-effectively resell a backup service to your clients.  For example, you can backup up to fifty sites for just $150 per year. Plus you can bring your own object storage like Amazon S3 which makes it super cheap to store tons of data.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\">BackUpBuddy by iThemes</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\">Pro Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3751 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"Best Backup Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin-400x130.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin-768x249.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a><br />\nIf you just have one site I recommend <a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\">VaultPress by Automattic</a>. This is what I personally use on this site and it&#8217;s a set it and forget it solution. Backups are stored offsite by <a href=\"https://automattic.com/\">Automattic</a> and restores are as easy as one click. Pricing starts at just $3.50 a month.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\">VaultPress by Automattic</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\">Pro Version</a></span><a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3752 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress.jpg\" alt=\"Best Backup Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress-400x130.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress-768x249.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#plugin-categories\">↑ Back to Plugin Categories</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"caching-plugins\">Best Caching Plugins</h2>\n<p>A caching plugin is another essential plugin you must have, especially if your host does not provide any caching. One of the best caching plugins out there is <a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\">WPRocket</a> and it&#8217;s what I use on this site. It has an excellent feature set and is very well supported and yes, it does make your website like a Rocket! :)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\"><strong>WPRocket</strong></a> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\">Pro Version</a></span><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3744 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket.jpg\" alt=\"Best Caching Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket-400x143.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket-768x275.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you are looking for a free just page caching plugin than look no further than <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\">WP Super Cache</a>. It has a lot fewer features than WP-Rocket but gets the job done.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\"><strong>WP Super Cache</strong></a> <span class=\"label label-success\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\">Free Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3745 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250.png\" alt=\"Best Caching Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"264\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250.png 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-400x137.png 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-768x263.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Some people might say, what about <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\">W3 Total Cache</a>. Well since this is my honest opinion I have had tons of issues with this plugin mostly due to the complexity and end users not knowing how to use it. If you are super technically maybe you&#8217;d enjoy it.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#plugin-categories\">↑ Back to Plugin Categories</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"#forms-plugins\">Best Forms (Contact Form) Plugins</h2>\n<p